                            <comment id="470131" author="sebastien" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2025 07:33:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ckansal&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ckansal&quot;&gt;ckansal&lt;/a&gt; there is no real way to automatically find the key, as it could be stored anywhere, and we could not guess which one to use. So admins need to decide which key they want to use for the mountpoint, and store it there as &lt;tt&gt;.lgss&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="470130" author="JIRAUSER19503" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2025 07:27:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sebastien&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sebastien&quot;&gt;sebastien&lt;/a&gt; Do we want the admin to &lt;b&gt;manually copy&lt;/b&gt; the key file to &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;mountpoint&amp;gt;/.lgss&lt;/tt&gt; before mounting? Or should our code &lt;b&gt;automatically find&lt;/b&gt; the key&#160;and copy it to &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;mountpoint&amp;gt;/.lgss&lt;/tt&gt; during the mount?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
